{"parse":{"title":"Shadow Cabinet of Alexis Tsipras","pageid":47527511,"revid":802817119,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"vertical-navbox nowraplinks vcard hlist\" style=\"float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%;border: 4px double #FA8072;\"><tbody><tr><th style=\"padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em;font-size: 110%; padding: 0; line-height: 150%;\"><table><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background:#FA8072; vertical-align:middle; padding:5px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Alexis_Tsipras_2015_(cropped).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Alexis Tsipras 2015 (cropped).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Alexis_Tsipras_2015_%28cropped%29.jpg/75px-Alexis_Tsipras_2015_%28cropped%29.jpg\" width=\"75\" height=\"112\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Alexis_Tsipras_2015_%28cropped%29.jpg/113px-Alexis_Tsipras_2015_%28cropped%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Alexis_Tsipras_2015_%28cropped%29.jpg/150px-Alexis_Tsipras_2015_%28cropped%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"298\" data-file-height=\"446\" /></a></td>\n<td style=\"background:#FA8072; vertical-align:middle; padding:6px;\"><span style=\"font-size:0.75em;\"><span style=\"color:#FFF\">This article is part of a series<br /> about</span></span><br /><span class=\"vcard\"><span class=\"fn\"><span style=\"font-size:0.95em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"Alexis Tsipras\"><span style=\"color:#FFF\">Alexis Tsipras</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding:0.3em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Athens_A\" title=\"Athens A\">MP for Athens A</a> (2009\u20132015)<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Heraklion_(regional_unit)\" title=\"Heraklion (regional unit)\">MP for Heraklion</a> (2015\u2013present)</li></ul>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Syriza\" title=\"Syriza\">Syriza</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Thessaloniki_Programme\" title=\"Thessaloniki Programme\">Thessaloniki Programme</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Shadow Cabinet</a></li></ul>\n<hr />\n<p><b>Prime Minister of Greece</b>\n</p>\n<small><div class=\"center\"><b>Jan\u2013Aug 2015; Sep 2015 \u2013 present</b></div></small>\n<hr />\n<p><b>First Government</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Greek_government_formation,_January_2015\" title=\"Greek government formation, January 2015\">Government formation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/First_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"First Cabinet of Alexis Tsipras\">First Tsipras cabinet</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Greek_bailout_referendum,_2015\" title=\"Greek bailout referendum, 2015\">2015 bailout referendum</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tenth_austerity_package_(Greece)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tenth austerity package (Greece)\">Tenth austerity package</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Eleventh_austerity_package_(Greece)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Eleventh austerity package (Greece)\">Eleventh austerity package</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Popular_Unity_(Greece)\" title=\"Popular Unity (Greece)\">Popular Unity</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Caretaker_Cabinet_of_Vassiliki_Thanou-Christophilou\" title=\"Caretaker Cabinet of Vassiliki Thanou-Christophilou\">Caretaker government</a></li></ul>\n<hr />\n<p><b>Second Government</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Greek_legislative_election,_September_2015\" title=\"Greek legislative election, September 2015\">September 2015 election</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Second_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"Second Cabinet of Alexis Tsipras\">Second Tsipras cabinet</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Twelfth_austerity_package_(Greece)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Twelfth austerity package (Greece)\">Twelfth austerity package</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Thirteenth_austerity_package_(Greece)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thirteenth austerity package (Greece)\">Thirteenth austerity package</a></li></ul>\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Alexis_Tsipras_Signature_(Greece_prime_minister).svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Alexis Tsipras Signature (Greece prime minister).svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Alexis_Tsipras_Signature_%28Greece_prime_minister%29.svg/120px-Alexis_Tsipras_Signature_%28Greece_prime_minister%29.svg.png\" width=\"120\" height=\"67\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Alexis_Tsipras_Signature_%28Greece_prime_minister%29.svg/180px-Alexis_Tsipras_Signature_%28Greece_prime_minister%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Alexis_Tsipras_Signature_%28Greece_prime_minister%29.svg/240px-Alexis_Tsipras_Signature_%28Greece_prime_minister%29.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"218\" data-file-height=\"122\" /></a></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%;text-align:center;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Alexis_Tsipras_sidebar\" title=\"Template:Alexis Tsipras sidebar\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Alexis_Tsipras_sidebar\" title=\"Template talk:Alexis Tsipras sidebar\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Alexis_Tsipras_sidebar&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b><a href=\"/wiki/Shadow_Cabinet\" title=\"Shadow Cabinet\">Shadow Cabinet</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"Alexis Tsipras\">Alexis Tsipras</a></b> was formed on 3 July 2012, following the <a href=\"/wiki/Greek_legislative_election,_June_2012\" title=\"Greek legislative election, June 2012\">June 2012 Greek legislative election</a>. It consisted of only <a href=\"/wiki/Syriza\" title=\"Syriza\">Syriza</a> MPs, as they were the largest party to refuse to participate in the <a href=\"/wiki/Cabinet_of_Antonis_Samaras\" title=\"Cabinet of Antonis Samaras\">ND-PASOK-DIMAR coalition</a>. The Shadow Cabinet was dissolved following the <a href=\"/wiki/Greek_legislative_election,_January_2015\" title=\"Greek legislative election, January 2015\">January 2015 Greek legislative election</a>, and was replaced by a <a href=\"/wiki/New_Democracy_(Greece)\" title=\"New Democracy (Greece)\">New Democracy</a> shadow cabinet led by <a href=\"/wiki/Antonis_Samaras\" title=\"Antonis Samaras\">Antonis Samaras</a>. Tsipras subsequently formed the <a href=\"/wiki/First_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"First Cabinet of Alexis Tsipras\">First Cabinet of Alexis Tsipras</a> on 27 January 2015, formed from a coalition of both Syriza and the <a href=\"/wiki/Independent_Greeks\" title=\"Independent Greeks\">Independent Greeks</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Role_of_shadow_ministers\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Role of shadow ministers</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Shadow_Cabinet_composition\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Shadow Cabinet composition</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Shadow_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Shadow Cabinet was formed on 3 July 2012, with the final composition being settled at a meeting of the Syriza parliamentary group at 11am on that day.<sup id=\"cite_ref-proto_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-proto-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The Shadow Cabinet acted in opposition to the <a href=\"/wiki/Cabinet_of_Antonis_Samaras\" title=\"Cabinet of Antonis Samaras\">Cabinet of Antonis Samaras</a>. Whilst in opposition, in December 2014, Syriza adopted the <a href=\"/wiki/Thessaloniki_Programme\" title=\"Thessaloniki Programme\">Thessaloniki Programme</a>, an economic manifesto.\n</p><p>The Shadow Cabinet would have officially remained in position until the 27 January 2015, when <a href=\"/wiki/Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"Alexis Tsipras\">Alexis Tsipras</a> named his new <a href=\"/wiki/First_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"First Cabinet of Alexis Tsipras\">Cabinet</a>. A number of members from the Shadow Cabinet took up roles in the new Cabinet.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Role_of_shadow_ministers\">Role of shadow ministers</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Shadow_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Role of shadow ministers\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The role of shadow ministers was to oversee the work being carried out by the government ministers and to offer alternative proposals. Syriza spokesman <a href=\"/wiki/Dimitrios_Papadimoulis\" title=\"Dimitrios Papadimoulis\">Dimitrios Papadimoulis</a> said: \"Syriza will be exercising hands-on, combative and responsible opposition, with strict oversight and also with its own proposals. It will be an opposition worthy of the 27 percent of the vote that put us in Parliament.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-handon_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-handon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Shadow_Cabinet_composition\">Shadow Cabinet composition</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Shadow_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Shadow Cabinet composition\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Leader_of_the_Opposition_(Greece)\" title=\"Leader of the Opposition (Greece)\">Leader of the Opposition</a> and Leader of <a href=\"/wiki/Syriza\" title=\"Syriza\">Syriza</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Alexis_Tsipras\" title=\"Alexis Tsipras\">Alexis Tsipras</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Minister_for_Foreign_Affairs_(Greece)\" title=\"Minister for Foreign Affairs (Greece)\">Minister for Foreign Affairs</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Rena_Dourou\" title=\"Rena Dourou\">Rena Dourou</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Minister_of_Finance_(Greece)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Minister of Finance (Greece)\">Minister of Finance</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Euclid_Tsakalotos\" title=\"Euclid Tsakalotos\">Euclid Tsakalotos</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_the_Interior_and_Administrative_Reconstruction\" title=\"Ministry of the Interior and Administrative Reconstruction\">Minister for the Interior</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Sofia_Sakorafa\" title=\"Sofia Sakorafa\">Sofia Sakorafa</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Economy,_Infrastructure,_Shipping_and_Tourism\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Economy, Infrastructure, Shipping and Tourism\">Development and Infrastructure Minister</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Giorgos_Stathakis\" title=\"Giorgos Stathakis\">Giorgos Stathakis</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Labour_and_Social_Solidarity_(Greece)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Labour and Social Solidarity (Greece)\">Labour Minister</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dimitris_Stratoulis&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Dimitris Stratoulis (page does not exist)\">Dimitris Stratoulis</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_the_Interior_and_Administrative_Reconstruction\" title=\"Ministry of the Interior and Administrative Reconstruction\">Minister for Administrative Reform</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Alexis_Mitropoulos&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Alexis Mitropoulos (page does not exist)\">Alexis Mitropoulos</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_the_Interior_and_Administrative_Reconstruction\" title=\"Ministry of the Interior and Administrative Reconstruction\">Minister for Citizen Protection</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dimitris_Tsoukalas&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Dimitris Tsoukalas (page does not exist)\">Dimitris Tsoukalas</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Productive_Reconstruction,_Environment_and_Energy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Productive Reconstruction, Environment and Energy\">Minister for the Environment</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Iro_Dioti&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Iro Dioti (page does not exist)\">Iro Dioti</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Productive_Reconstruction,_Environment_and_Energy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Productive Reconstruction, Environment and Energy\">Energy Minister</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thanassis_Petrakos&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Thanassis Petrakos (page does not exist)\">Thanassis Petrakos</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Health_and_Social_Security_(Greece)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Health and Social Security (Greece)\">Health Minister</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Andreas_Xanthos\" title=\"Andreas Xanthos\">Andreas Xanthos</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Minister_for_National_Defence_(Greece)\" title=\"Minister for National Defence (Greece)\">Minister for National Defence</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Economy,_Infrastructure,_Shipping_and_Tourism\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Economy, Infrastructure, Shipping and Tourism\">Shipping</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Thodoris_Dritsas\" title=\"Thodoris Dritsas\">Thodoris Dritsas</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Culture,_Education_and_Religious_Affairs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Culture, Education and Religious Affairs\">Education Ministers</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Tasos_Kourakis\" title=\"Tasos Kourakis\">Tasos Kourakis</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Theano_Fotiou\" title=\"Theano Fotiou\">Theano Fotiou</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Justice,_Transparency_and_Human_Rights\" title=\"Ministry of Justice, Transparency and Human Rights\">Justice Minister</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Zoi_Konstantopoulou\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Zoi Konstantopoulou\">Zoi Konstantopoulou</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Productive_Reconstruction,_Environment_and_Energy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Productive Reconstruction, Environment and Energy\">Minister for Agricultural Development</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Vangelis_Apostolou&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Vangelis Apostolou (page does not exist)\">Vangelis Apostolou</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Economy,_Infrastructure,_Shipping_and_Tourism\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Economy, Infrastructure, Shipping and Tourism\">Tourism Minister</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Michael_Kritsotakis&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Michael Kritsotakis (page does not exist)\">Michael Kritsotakis</a></li>\n<li>Shadow <a href=\"/wiki/Minister_for_Macedonia_and_Thrace\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Minister for Macedonia and Thrace\">Minister for Macedonia and Thrace</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Litsa_Amanatidou&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Litsa Amanatidou (page does not exist)\">Litsa Amanatidou</a></li>\n<li>Parliamentary Representative \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Panagiotis_Kouroumblis\" title=\"Panagiotis Kouroumblis\">Panagiotis Kouroumblis</a></li></ul>\n<p><small>References: <sup id=\"cite_ref-handon_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-handon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-deputies_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-deputies-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-skai_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-skai-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-tovima_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-tovima-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-tvxs_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-tvxs-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-proto_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-proto-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></small>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Shadow_Cabinet_of_Alexis_Tsipras&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-proto-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-proto_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-proto_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Makrygiannis, John (3 July 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=